Head (
Figs 4–6
) wide, rounded, dark green, vertex in the middle with wide blackish spot. Eyes large, broadly rounded, slightly exceeding anterior corners of pronotum, eye 0.91 times as wide as frons. Frons with weakly delimited black strip reaching to clypeus, epistome green. Clypeus black, with anterior margin straight. Vertex bare, frons with recumbent whitish pubescence. Cuticular sculpture of head prominent, consisting of polygonal cells with regularly elevated margins, without central grains. Inner surface of cells with microsculpture of minute cells. Width of eye the same as minimum interocular distance.

Legs slender, of variable colour. Femora and tibiae with microsculpture a sparsely with whitish pubescence. Fore femur ventrally golden-reddish, on inner margin smooth. Fore tibia (
Fig. 17
) on outer margin finely serrate, bent, on inner margin S- shaped with reddish setae on apical third, blackish from ventral side, greenish-red from dorsal side. Middle femur dorsally black, reddish-gold from ventral side. Middle tibia dorsally black, ventrally black with greenish tinge. Hind tibia straight, slightly S-shaped on inner margin.

Aedeagus (
Fig 21
) robust and wide. Penis flat, 4.28 times as long as wide, weakly sclerotized, with sharp apex. Parameres with broadened basis (here almost as wide as in median part), 2.71 times as long as wide. Parameral apices broad, with four conspicuous setae each.

Differential diagnosis .
Anthaxia tankenethi
sp. nov. differs from
A. gebhardti
by wider and more robust head; robust and oustanding eyes, minimum interocular distance larger than width of eye (minimum interocular distance shorter than width of eye in
A. gebhardti
); pronotum in the middle with cell-like cuticular structure (wrinkled structure in
A. gebhardti
); male fore tibia on outer (posterior) margin very finely, inconspicuously serrate or smooth (conspicuously serrate in
A. gebhardti
); body venter of various colouration – green, blue, reddish (uniformly green in
A. gebhardti
); anal ventrite of male deeply cut (ventrite of male inconspicuously cut apically in
A. gebhardti
).
